# Cloudflare Pages SPA fallback.
#
# React Router owns every path below the root (/login, /join, /student/assessments, …), but those
# paths are not files. Without this rule Pages answers a hard refresh — or the walkthrough's very
# first `goto('/login')` — with its own 404 page, and the app never boots. `200` rather than `301`
# so the URL the user typed survives into the router.
#
# This is a deployment artifact, not a React change: §57 makes the frontend the port's invariant
# and no component, service or type is touched by it.
/*    /index.html    200
